Data Analyst		1199SEIU Funds		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Responsibilities<br /></strong><ul><li> Provide support to the Assistant Director, and assist with systems administration and development, data analysis, and reporting </li> <li> Generate weekly and monthly reports to validate the accuracy of data extracted from Matchmaker system for external vendor files, (ADP, Vitech) </li> <li> Review, monitor and generate daily eligibility operating reports to ensure that participants benefits are not incorrectly suspended or terminated </li> <li> Act as a liaison with the IT department to respond and communicate discrepancies in the system to ensure resolution of database issues regarding benefits </li> <li> Analyze data and report system discrepancies and anomalies for correction </li> <li> Coordinate with Job Security Fund’s Supervisor and IT to review system anomalies and implement systematic changes </li> <li> Maintain communication with Job Service Coordinators regarding participant eligibility in the Job Security Fund </li> <li> Prepare and run weekly and monthly reports </li> <li> Must use reasoning ability to define problems, collect data, establish facts and draw valid conclusions </li> <li> Perform additional duties as assigned by management </li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>Qualifications<br /></strong><ul><li> Bachelor’s Degree or equivalent years of work experience in data analysis required </li> <li> Minimum two (2) years related experience and/ or training in benefits administration; and/or financial environment , or equivalent combination of education, experience, and training </li> <li> Bilingual (Spanish) preferred </li> <li> Advance knowledge of Microsoft Word and Excel; to include knowledge of Oracle and/or other financial programs preferred </li> <li> Strong mathematical ability to apply concepts such as addition, subtraction, fractions, decimals, and percentages to allocation of benefits </li> <li> Analytical and problem solving skills; able to indentify issues and troubleshoot to resolution </li> <li> Experience in understanding and implementing business rules and standard operating procedures </li> <li> Ability to maintain confidentiality of information, and interact with multiple system environments </li> <li> Excellent communication skills, both written and oral, including presentation skills </li> <li> Strong team player, with customer service and interpersonal skills </li> <li> Ability to prioritize, meet deadlines, plan and coordinate work in a time sensitive environment </li> <li> Ability to work flexible hours, including some evenings and weekends </li> <li> Must meet performance standards including attendance and punctuality</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">We are a Union of healthcare workers. We work in the homecare, hospital and nursing home industries, as well as pharmacies, freestanding clinics and other healthcare settings. We care for the sick, the infirm, the elderly. Ours is noble work. We are dedicated to our patients, our members and our families.<br /><br />The mission of our Union is to improve and expand quality patient care, to protect and improve the lives of our members and our families, and to work in solidarity with working people in our communities and around the world.<br /><br />In 1998, we affiliated to the Service Employees International Union (SEIU) which is, with 1.8 million healthcare and building service workers and public employees, the largest labor Union in North America.<br /><br />Since that time, some 15 SEIU healthcare Locals throughout New York State, the District of Columbia, Maryland and Massachusetts have merged with 1199 and today are part of 1199SEIU United Healthcare Workers East.</div>